originalText: Who needs a spleen? No, really... it's not a vital organ.
People ask me all the time, "What are your favorite kinds of injuries to treat?" My answer: Spinal injuries - they are interesting to the bone!
I just happen to have a patient that is missing an arm. Care to donate?
People ask me all the time: "Why do you keep the dead next to the living? It's not hygienic!" I never reply. ::Laughs.::
And then he said, "But doc, that procedure is going to kill me!" ::Laughs.:: It actually did. Who would've guessed?
One day you too will die. Expert opinion. ::Laughs.::
People ask me all the time, "How do you dispose of the dead?" My answer: I just toss them in the chute; it's more fun than it looks.
I dissected my first eel when I was five. My first human? Six or seven years old. Feels like yesterday.
Do you have any spare kidneys I could borrow? Did I say borrow? ::Laughs.:: I meant forcefully remove.
People always complain about the smell, but I smell nothing. Literally - nothing!
I sometimes get the living and the dead mixed up in here. They all just look so... mangled.
Watch your step! I dropped an eyeball.

description: 前後のテキストの状況を示すヒントになるかも
